28. Use image.asset to add image in Flutter App Development

✅ Explanation (Exam-Oriented)

In Flutter, the Image.asset widget is used to display images stored locally in the project.

Loads images from the assets folder
Commonly used for logos, icons, and UI images
Requires configuration in pubspec.yaml
💻 Steps to Add Image
Create folder → assets/images/
Add image (e.g., sample.png)
Update pubspec.yaml:

//pubspec.yaml
flutter:
  assets:
    - assets/images/sample.png

//main code
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: ImageExample(),
    );
  }
}

class ImageExample extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text("Image.asset Example"),
      ),
      body: Center(
        child: Image.asset(
          'assets/images/sample.png',
          width: 200,
          height: 200,
          fit: BoxFit.cover,
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}